# Reflection on Coding in Markdown (STAR Method)

## Situation

During this portfolio project, I was required to create a professional digital portfolio using GitHub and Markdown language. The goal was to present my skills, experience, CV, and mock interview evidence in a clean and organized format.

## Task

My task was to learn how Markdown works and use it correctly to structure my portfolio professionally. I needed to include headings, lists, links, formatting, and multimedia elements while ensuring the portfolio remained easy to read and visually appealing.

## Action

I researched Markdown syntax and practiced using different formatting techniques such as headings, bullet points, hyperlinks, and embedded media. I organized my portfolio into sections including my profile, education, skills, experience, projects, and references. I also used GitHub to manage and upload my files effectively.

## Result

Through this process, I improved my technical documentation skills and gained a better understanding of how developers use Markdown for professional communication. I was able to create a structured and professional portfolio that clearly presents my information and demonstrates my growing technical abilities.

