# Reflection on the Use of GitHub Pages (STAR Method)

## Situation

For this assessment, I was required to publish my digital portfolio using GitHub Pages so that it could be accessed online.

## Task

My task was to successfully deploy my portfolio to GitHub Pages and ensure that all content, links, and formatting displayed correctly on the live website.

## Action

I created and managed my repository on GitHub, uploaded my Markdown files, and configured GitHub Pages for deployment. I tested the live website multiple times to ensure the portfolio loaded correctly and that all sections were accessible and properly formatted.

## Result

By completing this task, I gained practical experience using GitHub Pages for web hosting and portfolio deployment. I improved my understanding of version control, repository management, and online publishing. The final result was a professional online portfolio that showcases my skills and work readiness evidence.
